               tolType => 'absolute',
               tolerance => .000000000000000000001,   );          
    </pg-code>

    <statement>
      <p>Use the graphs of trigonometric functions to find the following information. </p>
        <p>
          (a) <m>\cos 0 = </m> <var name="$ans1" width="6"/>
        </p>
        <p>
        (b) <m>\tan \pi = </m> <var name="$ans2" width="6"/>
        </p>
        <p>
        (c) All values of <m>x</m> in the interval <m>[-2\pi, 2\pi]</m> where <m>\sin x = -1</m>. <var name="$ans3" width="6"/>
        </p>
    </statement>
  </webwork>
</exercise>

<p> 
Graphs also illustrate symmetries. For example, <m>y=\sin \theta</m> and <m>y=\tan \theta</m> are odd functions, while <m>y=\cos \theta</m> is an even function.
</p>
<p>
Recall that a function <m>f(x)</m> is an <term>odd function</term> if <m>f(-x)=-f(x)</m> for all <m>x</m> in the domain of <m>f</m>. Visually, this means that the graph has 180 degree symmetry about the origin.
</p>
<p>
 Also, <m>f(x)</m> is an <term>even function</term> if <m>f(-x)=f(x)</m> for all <m>x</m> in the domain of <m>f</m>. This means that the graph of <m>f</m> has reflective symmetry about the <m>y</m>-axis. 
</p>

   <p>
     <example xml:id="graph2">
    <title>Symmetries</title>
    <statement>
      <p>
      Which of the following statements are true, and which are false? 
      </p>
      <p>
      <nl>
      <li>
        <p>
          (a) <m>y=\tan x</m> is an odd function. 
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
          (b) <m>y=\sec x</m> is an odd function. 
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
        (c) <m>\sin \left(\frac{3}{8}\right) = - \sin \left(-\frac{3}{8}\right)</m>
        </p>
      </li>
    </nl>
      </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        (a) True
      </p>
      <p>
        (b) False
      </p>      
      <p>
        (c) True
      </p>      
    </answer>
    <solution>
       <p>
        (a) This is true. Looking at the graph we see that it is symmetric about the origin. 
      </p>
      <p>
        (b) This is false. Looking at the graph we see that it is symmetric about the <m>y</m>-axis, so this is an even function, not odd. 
      </p>      
      <p>
        (c) This is true. This is a property of odd functions and <m>y=\sin x </m> is an odd function. 
      </p>    
    </solution>
  </example>
     </p>

